{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/diagnosis/clinical-features/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"b7088810-465b-5e01-81ca-9d367eed71ef","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 47693cab-046a-4628-b70b-1787f2603693 --><h2>When should I suspect pre-patellar bursitis?</h2><!-- end field 47693cab-046a-4628-b70b-1787f2603693 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 442bfc6f-001c-496b-8ae0-2ae34ce68770 --><!-- begin field a283adf0-ef4f-419c-b865-793c25760b18 --><ul><li><strong>Suspect pre-patellar bursitis if:</strong><ul><li>There is localized swelling over the patella.<ul><li>The area may be mildly tender and slightly warm to touch in acute bursitis.</li><li>The person may report intermittent swelling with chronic bursitis.</li></ul></li><li>The swelling is fluctuant (movable and compressible) — the patella may not be palpable with large collections of fluid.</li><li>There is a normal range of joint movement (depending on the size of the fluid collection). This is in contrast to septic arthritis.</li><li>The person reports maximal discomfort at extreme flexion of the knee (when the swollen bursa is compressed).</li><li>The person has a history of preceding trauma or bursal disease (from previous traumatic bursitis, rheumatoid arthritis, or gout).</li></ul></li><li><strong>It may be difficult to differentiate clinically between septic and non-septic bursitis</strong> — aspiration of the affected bursa may be needed for a definitive diagnosis.<ul><li>Features that may indicate septic bursitis include:<ul><li>Systemic features such as fever, nausea or malaise.</li><li>Pain and tenderness to palpation.</li><li>Erythema and overlying warmth.</li><li>Local cellulitis.</li><li>A visible port of entry for micro-organisms such as abrasion or laceration over the bursa.</li><li>Immunocompromised state.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Suspect an alternative diagnosis if:</strong><ul><li>There is generalized joint swelling.</li><li>The range of knee movement is limited and painful.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field a283adf0-ef4f-419c-b865-793c25760b18 --><!-- end item 442bfc6f-001c-496b-8ae0-2ae34ce68770 -->","topic":{"id":"7c029d3e-557f-550b-885f-a4fbb6ea8b1a","topicId":"54c9032c-42d1-4a7e-aa9b-60cc7c1f66b7","topicName":"Pre-patellar bursitis","slug":"pre-patellar-bursitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2016","chapters":[{"id":"a3d36f54-4e47-50ed-adae-8c2966e52581","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bace3ffb-9b9e-509e-8531-d66d3c3c62b8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f4c8ac50-2d63-5270-a56e-0a3146cc2f4b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"b2ab9579-f5ec-589c-81d9-3041f5c94af1","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"98917828-0ada-5354-9717-48e2b11fef87","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"aebfa517-bad1-5890-b277-d9b97452caf0","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"710d52f9-ba68-5428-a898-b6c7edc2e769","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"0f5f5f23-030a-55f7-bb30-e90a7a6b3b4e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"dc55f8b1-83f2-529f-b685-722d05af1144","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8af4ee05-9fd0-5411-b646-4349b701edf7","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"81aa996e-fa7d-541a-aacf-177f62da0eb9","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"030b0978-9d73-568a-97ff-ff7eb2372e81","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"410c4858-f373-5a79-9d91-0341834ece97","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"75c14afe-d269-5f9e-9fd7-b115134e3571","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"955fe314-c2f6-59b3-b2db-3e1696f263db","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"cc360743-59d8-514a-a911-cc17de6aa607","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"1f7d09df-a6ff-5a6b-a2ad-e6c9c72b8755","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"8d7981ca-5740-5233-80da-a5b6e134534b","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"5a41072a-faa5-541c-9411-ffa969d2479d","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"b7088810-465b-5e01-81ca-9d367eed71ef","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features"},{"id":"9dc06e96-e790-5daf-8048-4f8156b87cf8","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"a8210e9d-2644-5c40-8fb6-d977678e40ff","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"},{"id":"a5f53d74-d84e-5651-ba73-4a6f40b49d95","slug":"aspiration-of-pre-patellar-bursitis","fullItemName":"Aspiration of pre-patellar bursitis"}]},{"id":"6ba64df6-3247-5525-8923-93745e4f9256","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"7932f090-0d2e-5ad6-8870-388ca16b89d7","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"d83f3a5e-9002-57cc-b1e5-4fc4b6456658","fullItemName":"Prescribing information","slug":"prescribing-information","subChapters":[{"id":"33232327-f459-5cc2-8bab-5d4f04bbb3d3","slug":"analgesia","fullItemName":"Analgesia"}]},{"id":"b3e0c735-ba47-55c9-b748-1039fc782f6d","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"c0171a2d-90a6-52ef-8ad8-8f6aa759b04c","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"3bf641c1-7809-5fa0-8a24-86be2a800942","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"fa4628ed-f42b-5665-9923-827df63b1414","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"861000f2-c3de-52df-b001-757afd7049d8","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"84ce47d8-9128-5472-a449-bbb9b4749a01","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"793cc2bd-ba79-52bb-a616-df2f7f376d54","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"8d12b54e-612b-5890-bfdd-84eb0660aaa3","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"5a41072a-faa5-541c-9411-ffa969d2479d","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"9ad9662a-1efe-5201-a7c4-a9ee1852cd8f","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-b82","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 7787ff67-6c23-45ff-8fdc-811fdc433817 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 7787ff67-6c23-45ff-8fdc-811fdc433817 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b82163dc-2da2-482a-a9cd-93db8f44309f --><!-- begin field 162337e1-0694-4a40-93b2-19b639e2927f --><p>The recommendations on the clinical features and clinical differentiation of septic and non-septic bursitis are based on the clinical guideline from the American College of Occupational and Environmental Medicine <em>Knee disorders</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">ACOEM, 2011</a>] and expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Aaron et al, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Chalmers, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Hanrahan, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Baumbach et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Hong, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2016</a>].</p><ul><li>The literature highlights the difficulties of clinically distinguishing septic from non-septic bursitis due to the overlap of clinical features.<ul><li>Bursal swelling, redness, and tenderness are inadequate to differentiate between septic and non-septic bursitis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Baumbach et al, 2014</a>].</li><li>Aspiration is often necessary to distinguish between septic and non-septic bursitis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pre-patellar-bursitis/references/\">Aaron et al, 2011</a>].</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 162337e1-0694-4a40-93b2-19b639e2927f --><!-- end item b82163dc-2da2-482a-a9cd-93db8f44309f -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}